         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">16/2/79 ¶ I write a few lines to you, dear Dr Beccari, assuming that by this time you have quietly settled down at your post in Florence, and altho' ¶  ¶ you will not rest on your ¶  ¶ " ¶ laurels ¶ "...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.02.16</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Odoardo Beccari</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">University of Florence, Science Library: Botany, Archives, Beccari 12/32</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">16/2/79</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">I write a few lines to you, dear Dr Beccari, assuming that by this time you have quietly settled down at your post in Florence, and altho'<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>you will not rest on your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">laurels</hi>
               </seg>", you will doubtless now — after having faced so many dangers and earned so much<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"glory"<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>— proceed to publish regularly your researches, and enjoy the quietness of settled literary life with — I hope — a happy household.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I look forward with much interest to the continuation of your important<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Malesia".<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Beccari (1877-90).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Recently I have reviewed a small collection of plants from Mr Goldie and several other collections from the missionary The Reverend J. Chalmers. The specimens are mostly too imperfect for accurate examination, still I may manage to publish on them 16 pages more (No VI) of the Papuan plants.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Part VI of Papuan plants, B85.06.03, was not published for some time, and contained no plants contributed by Goldie.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>The species, which I recognize are nearly all known, only about 3 or 4 new ones; and as your Papuan collections came all from the N. W. and those obtained for me are all from the S. E., it is not likely that we shall clash in any<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">minor</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>publication of mine.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your Sumatra &amp; Borneo collections must also be teaming<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>teeming?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>with so much novelty that you can well afford to leave a few novelties to me. Kindly consider, that unless I can go on with the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Papuan plants", I shall have nothing to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">encourage</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the Missionaries to continue their sendings to me. Among the plants recently received from New Guinea are spec of the following genera not yet mentioned in my<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>"Papuan plants": Oxalis, Mollinedia Aristotelia Gomphrena, Coccoloba, Alphitonia, Elatostemma, Carumbium, Chloranthus, Nauclea, Eryth[rinia]<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>uncertain transcription: interlined.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Vittadinia Centipeda, Dichrocephala, Crepis, Eranthemum, Physalis, Diospyros, Coleus, Spathoglottis, Dianella, Tacca, Smilax, Aneilema, Habenaria, Pennisetum, Sporobolus, Chionachne, Isachne, Ophioglossum, &amp;c, (the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sp.</hi>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>nearly all well known).</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>You will be<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sad</hi>
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>to learn, that our generous friend, Chev. Marinucci, died suddenly last month from intestinal inflammation.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn4" n="5">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Italian Consul-General to Australia died on 6 February 1879 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 7 February 1879, p. 5, col. a)</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>What a kind and excellent man he was, particularly attached to myself. I shall miss<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>him very much indeed, and the Italian Government will find it difficult to obtain so excellent a Representative again.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">With regardful remembrance your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When you send me any N. Guin, plants, then please send the Leguminosae first.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn5" n="6">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marginal note, p. 1.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Dr Scheffer sent a large lot of Rubiaceae of Dutch India, but they [are] all described in Miquels volumes.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn6" n="7">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marginal note, p. 2.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Reference may be to<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Miquel (1855-9).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>My best salutation to Dr Giglioli.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn7" n="8">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Marginal note, p. 3.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
